The difficulties are already starting to appear. I'll probably have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's position with regards to certain medicines.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUS amounts of time and require A LOT of extra work.
Although it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve and, for now, it seems *completely* surmountable. It's just that it will take a lot of time and $$$.
Just in case the challenge that awaits you is interesting.
The FAA isn't a fan of TDAH. They don't issue a medical certificate if you're following treatment for that.
